                            <comment id="418227" author="ssmirnov" created="Tue, 18 Jun 2024 17:06:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue can manifest itself in two ways and there are two separate causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If Netlink is used for communication between the user-space and the kernel, then it appears that the design prevents tunables from being added to the message&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If Netlink is detected to be not suppored the &quot;old API&quot; is used, and in that case there&apos;s an alignment problem caused by wrong padding in &quot;struct lnet_ioctl_config_ni&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
